312250.name: number_nondem_bmr_owid
312250.description: The variable denotes the number of non-democracies based on the classification by Boix et al. (2013).
312250.datasetName: Regime numbers - OWID based on Boix et al. (2013), L端hrmann et al. (2018), V-Dem (v12), OWID (2021)

source.name: OWID based on Boix et al. (2013), L端hrmann et al. (2018), V-Dem (v12)
source.dataPublishedBy: Our World in Data, Bastian Herre
source.dataPublisherSource: Data on regimes comes from Boix et al. (2013), the Varieties of Democracy project (v12), using L端hrmann et al's (2018) classification, and own expansions and refinements.
source.additionalInfo:
This dataset provides information on the number of countries having different political systems.

Political regimes are identified using either Boix et al. (2013), or the Regimes of the World classification from L端hrmann et al. (2018) using data from the Varieties of Democracy Project (v12), and expanding the data and refining the classification ourselves.

The classification by Boix et al. (2013) distinguishes between democracies and non-democracies.

The Regimes of the World classification distinguishes between closed autocracies, electoral autocracies, electoral democracies, and liberal democracies. You can read a detailed description of the data in this post: https://ourworldindata.org/regimes-of-the-world-data

You can download the code and complete dataset, including supplementary variables, from GitHub: https://github.com/owid/notebooks/tree/main/BastianHerre/political_regimes
